					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1375">Everfrost</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Staff of the Wheel</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Staff of the Wheel</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=194796"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Dagorlok Eldaril</a> | 
		                        9/25/2000 11:36:27 AM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2"><B><I><U><P>Staff of the Wheel.</P>
</I></U><P>The Complete Spoiler</B>.</P>
<FONT FACE="Tempus Sans ITC"><P>Tarton had a wheel</P>
<P>That once he built</P>
<P>Ten spokes to wood</P>
<P>Bound by a Star</P>
<P>Tarton had a wheel,</P>
<P>To roam the Planes</P>
<P>Shaped twice by Ice</P>
<P>To guide his way</P>
<P>Tarton had a wheel</P>
<P>That once he lost</P>
<P>Clash in the Sky</P>
<P>To earth he fell</P>
<P>Tarton had a wheel</P>
<P>Was sundered past </P>
<P>The pieces scattered</P>
<P>Across the world </P>
<P>- <B>The Tome of the Wheel</B> </P>
</FONT><P>The Staff of the Wheel is a Wizard only quest, which involves finding magical rods that are scattered about Norrath in unlikely (and sometimes difficult) places. Combining the rods successfully yields not only the Staff of the Wheel, but also the Star of Eyes. These two items can be kept or given back to Sulgar in return for the Runes of Frost and Astral, which are necessary components for the level 49 Research only spell, <B>Ice Comet</B>, which is inarguably the most powerful DD spell within Everquest (exclusive of the Kunark expansion). All the items and resultants are LORE and/or NO DROP. I have been warned that this Rune of the Astral <U>does not combine</U> with the Rune of Impetus if you wanted to use it for the other level 49 spell, <B>Super Nova</B>.</P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2><P> <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/files2/ITM_221225_22080.jpg"></P>
<P>Staff of the Wheel</B> </P>
<P>MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>
Skill: 1HB Atk Delay: 100<BR>
DMG: 10<BR>
+10 INT, +10 HP, +10 MANA<BR>
WT: 1.0<BR>
Class: WIZ<BR>
Race: HUM, ERU, HIE, DEF, GNM</P>
</FONT><P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2><P>Star of Eyes</B><BR>
MAGIC ITEM NO DROP <BR>
Effect: Identify (Unlimited charges)<BR>
WT: 0.1<BR>
Class: WIZ<BR>
Race: HUM, ERU, HIE, DEF, GNM</P>
</FONT><P> </P>
<P>The person who gives this quest is a Wizard named Sulgar. You can find him by going to the northernmost edge of Everfrost and travelling East from there. At around 3013,-2396, you will see a white robed male NPC and two female barbarians. Hail Sulgar and follow the keywords. He will give you a Tome with clues to the locations of the rods and a 10 place Combine Box called the "Wheel Case" in conversation or the "Glowing Chest" when opened.  You do not need the Wheel Case to do the quest, only to complete it.</P>
<P> WARNING: The Wheel Case Box is a NOSAVE, which means if you log out with it, it goes *Poof* <U>along with everything in it</U>! </P>
<P>Don’t put any rods in the case until you have them ALL and are ready to Combine! I recommend getting all the rods FIRST, saving the Beza rune for last, just before you go to Sulgar, since it is fairly easy to acquire and close geographically. Also, there are other items in the game (like the Scepter of Sorrows) that look just like the rods, obtainable from some of the same zones. I recommend using Identify to make sure that you have the correct rods BEFORE you click Combine or risk the ugly consequences. This appears to be the source of some of the failures to successfully complete the quest. </P>
<P>Details for each Rod and some tactics for getting them are below. In general, I use Invisibility the entire time to avoid unwanted confrontations, but it is not a panacea so don’t depend on it keeping you safe. Con all NPC’s and remember that they will all be Indifferent to you when you are under the influence of Invisibility.  Most of the rods are obtained from underwater sources and several are a very long swim.  Buy at least 2 vials of Fish Gill extract before starting this quest solo.</P>
<OL>

<LI>AZIA - This rod is located in Erud’s Crossing on the deep part of the ocean floor past the shipwreck, location -1162, 2340. Beware of the Zombie Sailors in the shipwreck unless you just want to clean them out ahead of time. As of this writing there are 3 Killer Sharks guarding the rod. These sharks hit very hard, 100+, are 40+ in level. If they aggro, you are not going to last long (I certainly didn’t) and due to the visibility in the water it will be a difficult corpse retrieval. In any case, I recommend binding on the island before trying any of the tactics outlined below.</LI></OL>


<UL>

<UL>
<LI>After unsuccessfully trying several other strategies, a Druid friend of mine <I>cast Invis to Animals</I> on me as a test and it worked perfectly. The 3 sharks guarding this rod can definitely see through regular <I>Invis</I>, but apparently not <I>Invis to Animals</I>. I only tried this once and didn’t hang around long, but two of us were down there and they ignored us both. (Thanks to Stroh and Ayanosuke of Sanctuary)</LI>
<LI>One strategy is to use <I>Levitate</I> to hang above the site in the air/water boundary zone so that you can see the sharks circling at the bottom. <I>See Invisible</I> will also give you a similar effect when the spell flashes. Rumors are that two of the sharks come head to head every few minutes or so. This means they are fighting and occupied, (leaving only one shark to deal with?). Swim down quickly and scoop up the rod. </LI>
<LI>This entire quest is made much easier by use of Shiny Brass Idols. (Lore, expendable). These marvelous things will make you invulnerable for about 18 seconds. Buy one from groups that have been hunting in High Pass Hold, or slay the named Orc, Vulpok Shralok (Lvl 24) yourself. Shralok spawns at the Kithicor zone Orc area. A handy trick is to swim and levitate to a point 250 units directly south of the rod piece and use true north to point you directly at it. Swim quickly down and pick it up as quickly as possible, using your Shiny Brass Idol (only) if needed. </LI></UL>
</UL>

<OL>

<LI>BEZA - Do this rod either first or last.  Sulgar is close at hand in Everfrost so it makes for a convenient spot to bind without losing any tactical advantage.  In Everfrost, within the underwater caves, there is a "house" all the way back in the caves, where three Ice Boned Skeletons guard it in the center of the room. To find the hole in the ice that leads to the underwater cave, go to +2420, -4060. Bind yourself either here or someplace close at hand (Trust me on this). Swim directly north to the caves, not a difficult entrance to find. You may or may not need enduring breath for this swim depending on your swimming skill. At a skill level of 130, I had plenty of air for the swim but I had a bottle of Fish Gill Extract ready just in case. Once you hit dry land inside the cave, keep right the whole way until you reach the "house". It is not a difficult pickup, the IBSkellies are green to me at 26, but be careful on the way out! Verant may have thrown in a little surprise for the unwary, it would appear that picking the rod may trigger a spawn of the <B><FONT SIZE=2>Lich of Miragul, </B></FONT>a level 50+ NPC with a Pet. Miragul is part of the Fiery Avenger quest. Be alert. If you see him, GATE immediately. Don’t try to slip past even with Invisibility, or you will die in nothing flat. Many people on this quest have run into him (I did), always on the way out so its either an odd coincidence or a trigger.</LI>
<LI>CAZA - In Lake Rathe in a Aqua Goblin Tower.  You will need a friendly Bard, Enduring Breath, or an equivalent, such as several vials of Fish Gill Extract for this rod. From the South Karana zone border, straight out from the dock is an island with the Aviak Guard tower on it. Underneath that island is an underwater tunnel. The entrance to the tunnel faces West, towards Arena. (Loc 2622,1458). This is a <U>very long tunnel</U> so check your Invis before you enter the main chamber. After you get out of the tunnel and into the main chamber continue to swim straight ahead (directly east) which will lead you to a stone tower. The rod is on the top floor of the tower, accessible from the window and is guarded by high level aqua goblins. There appears to have been some "adjustment" in this zone recently because one of the Aqua Goblins conned blue to my Level 51 Minstrel friend, who subsequently died (just after I did.) At that level they see through Invis., but aggro range is fairly short. They do not appear to aggro until you enter the tower room.</LI></OL>


<UL>
<LI>Tactic one is to Bind yourself on the Guard Island and have a friend just kill you off via duel. Trying to recover your corpse under the island is ugly, so loot a bottle of Fish Gill extract off your corpse and go down naked to "kamikaze" the rod. When you enter the top room of the tower you’re going to get hit fast and hard. Place the Rod in your Inventory first then bolter as far as you can. When you respawn next to your first corpse, you can more easily recover your second corpse since you’ll still have your stuff. </LI>
<LI>Tactic two involves swimming to a position just outside and above the window where the rod is. Stop swimming and allow yourself to drift down past the window. If executed correctly, you will be able to snag the rod <U>without</U> entering the room, thus avoiding the aggro (and resulting death) altogether. This works, I can attest to it, but it scared the life out of me. Be ready to inventory the Rod and swim or Gate out of there.</LI></UL>

<P> </P>
<OL>

<LI>DENA - Dagnor's Cauldron, right outside the entrance to Kedge Keep. From the entrance to Unrest, facing the island, there is a tall pillar of rock just to the right, freestanding at the water’s edge. Directly down slope from this is the entrance to Kedge. Face with your back to the Kedge entrance, line yourself up with the fallen pillar to your left and swim downward. You will be in a little gully, so follow the gully down until you see the rod. This rod is very deep at location –886,-743,-430, but is do-able without Enduring Breath if your swimming skill is around 125 or better.</LI>
<LI>ENA- Lower Guk in the Reanimated Hand room. This one can be a truly horrible task even if you’re familiar with both levels of Guk. The Reanimated Hand spawns in the Hand Room, along with about 8 other spawns, including Dry Bone Skeletons, Barbed Bone Skeletons, Skeletal Monks, Carrion Ghouls, and occasionally a Werebat. The Reanimated Hand is a level 25 wizard. It hits for 20-50 damage, and casts spells doing 100-150dmg. In order to even get to the RH room, you will need someone to cast Invis to Undead on you.  Regular Invis will not work with the Undead.  Also remember that Vampire Bats, Werebats etc. are not undead so they will see you through the Invis-Undead</LI></OL>


<UL>
<LI>Tactic one. Like the Runes of Scale, the Rods are Wiz only Lore/Nodrop so nobody else wants them. Go when the Hand is camped, during heavy server usage times. Wait until the Hand and any Dar Knight have been pulled to the room under the floating water, and just swim up and get the rod then gate out of there. The floor is almost the same color as the rod in this room, making it somewhat difficult to see.</LI>
<LI>Go with a full group of Level 25's and kill off the Hand & Company yourself.</LI>
<LI>Kamikaze is always an option. If you elect to use this tactic or have no other choice, remember to slot the rod in your inventory first, then jump in the floating water to make your corpse easier to retrieve since the Hand will not aggro you in the water when you go to retrieve your corpse.</LI></UL>

<OL>

<LI>FANA – Is located in the center of Oasis, close to the Specter tower. Like the Lake Rathe rod, it is located on the top floor of an underwater tower. This tower is not underneath the Specter Tower on the island, but in the little bay close to the inn. The rod is on the top floor of the tower, which is open at the sides and top. I just swam down and picked it up. The Deepwater goblins guarding this treasure were green to me at 26, so they didn’t aggro on me. If you are attempting the quest below that level, beware than many DW Goblin Spellcasters can see through Invis. If they con blue or higher, you might have to consider one of the tactics explained previously.</LI>
<LI>GEZA - Highhold Pass. It is in the water near the waterfall closest to the Tiger Inn, there are 2 waterfalls there, rod is in front of the one closest to the inn. It is unguarded and easy to find.</LI>
<LI>HEDA - Is found in the Qeynos Aqueducts, in the shark pit there, but Invis will take care of that. The closest entrance is to the left of the Qeynos main gate, through the hidden door that looks like vines.</LI>
<LI>IZAH – In Neriak in the water outside the back of the bar called "The Blind Fish", the bar has 4 glass windows that are underwater, and the rod spawns right in front of one of those windows. The rod is pickable through the leftmost window so you don’t even have to get your robe wet. The only danger here is having your Invis drop when close to a guard if you’re KOS. If you do not know Neriak or are not welcomed there, I suggest creating a newbie Dark Elf to get familiar with the waterway area, the guards, and the location of the rod before attempting to grab this one. There are MANY guards that patrol the bridge area but you will be safe once in the water.</LI>
<LI>JAKA – In the Estate of Unrest. Get this one right after the DENA rod. Enter Unrest and follow the right hand wall around past the Gazebo until you get to the small river. It’s in the water (what a surprise) down a short passage. The passage entrance is close to the first bend in the river, closest to the gazebo and is pretty easy to find. If you know where the Gnome Spelunker is, instead of going into the tunnel that leads to him, go to the other side of the creek, toward the mansion.  Invis Vs Undead would be good here as the Tormented Dead like a refreshing swim from time to time also.</LI></OL>

<P>That completes the spoiler. I would like to thank many people that have contributed to this knowledge base and wish you all good questing.  If there are any errors or omissions, please post them here and I will attempt to correct and repost this spoiler.</P>
<P>Regards,</P>
<B><FONT FACE="Lucida Handwriting"><P>Dagorlok Eldaril</B></FONT>  – Sanctuary on the Nameless </P>
<FONT SIZE=2><P> </P>
</FONT><B><P>Notes:</P>
</B><FONT SIZE=2><P>A previous bug reported where the rods only respawned at long intervals has been fixed. Rods now respawn almost immediately.</P>
<P>Failures to Combine successfully are generally due to the wrong ingredients, not skill level.  Use "Identify" to make sure you have the correct rods.</P>
</FONT><P> </P>
<B><P>Acknowledgements:</P>
</B><P>Tumlaar of E’ci</P>
<P>Fnagaton Blazemaker of Bristlebane</P>
<P>Synge Drakesphyre of Prexus</P>
<P>Talisin Sa`Lidar</P>
<P>Aldein of Nameless</P>
