	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Lazy bum quest was already posted =) didn't do this quest myself as Im no where near high enough to use Ice Comet (although the +10int on the staff would be nice...) but here's a post from the other quest thread that should answer your question:<BR>
<BR>
&quot;--Submited by:  Tumlaar of E'ci On: 9/22/1999 6:44:31 PM    <BR>
Here are the rod locations for the ice comet quest, which begins by talking to Sulgar in Everfrost. Once you ahve the rods you go to him and ask him for the chest which you need to combine the rods. <BR>
Upon a succesful combining of the rods (which is hard, i failed 3 out of 5 times), <BR>
you make 2 items, one is the staff of the wheel (see stats below) <BR>
the other is the star of eyes (see statss below) <BR>
which you can either keep or give to him for the runes.<BR>
<BR>
Anyhow the locations are as follows,<BR>
<BR>
1. Azia- is correct in Eruds crossing on the deep part of the ocean floor past the boat, locatiom -1162 pos 2340<BR>
2. Beza- COrrect in the underwater caves, it is in the &quot;house&quot; all the way back and right in the cave, where 3 dry bones guard it in the center of the room.<BR>
3. Caza- Lake rathe, Under neath the first island you see is an underwater tnnel leading to a stone tower, its on the top floor of the tower (need enduring breath for this one)<BR>
4. Dena. Dagnor's cauldron, right outside the entrance to kedge, if you face with your back to kedge, is directly diagagnal left, in a corner.<BR>
5. ENA- Lower Gukk in the Reanimated hand room. This one is the only one you need a group for, unless your brave and kamakazi it. Warning the floor is the same color as the rod in this room and it makes it very hard to find with the hand and the dar beating on you.<BR>
6. Fana- Oasis is correct but the tower is underwater next to the above ground tower, this one is on the top floor of the tower as well.<BR>
7. Geza- HH pass is correct, its in the water near the waterfall closest <BR>
to the Tiger Inn, there are 2 waterfalls there, rod is in front of the one closest to the inn.<BR>
8. Heda- Erudin is Wrong, it is Qeynos Aquceducts, in the shark pit there.<BR>
9. Izah- Neriak is correct, but its in the water in front of the bar called &quot;the blind fish&quot;, the bar has 4 glass windows that are underwater, and the rod spawns right infront of those windows.<BR>
10.Jaka- Its in unrest but not near a mob that drops dwarven armor, its in the water outside the right side of the house near wherer the the gnome spelunker is, instead of goin into the tunnel that leads to him, you go a little right of that entracnce and theres a very short passage, there lies the rod.<BR>
<BR>
I hope this helps, its 100% accurate, if you dont beleive me i can show you my staff of the wheel:)<BR>
<BR>
Also like to add that the rods only spawn after server resets, and they are no drop so once some newb picks em up, they are gone till a server reset.<BR>
<BR>
Also out of 5 times i failed on combining the rods 3 times. The runes of frost and astral are no drop from the quest as is the scroll they make. Also the rune of astral does not work with the rune of impetus if you wanted to use it for the other lvl 49 spell you can make astral.<BR>
<BR>
Stats on Staff of the Wheel is 10dmg 100delay 10int 10hp 10mana 1hb Wiz only.<BR>
Star of eyes is a jewel that can cast unlimited identify spell.&quot;<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
